{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019RBhfhE7HTSbUHjiC56wp2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was done and how:\n\n**Setup analysis:**\n- Elasticsearch 8.11.1 bundles `repository-s3` as a **module** (not a plugin), so it's available out of the box\n- The `es-secure-settings` Secret contained `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` (both `minioadmin`)\n- The Secret was mounted at `/mnt/secure-settings`, but Elasticsearch reads credentials only from its **keystore** — the keystore already had the credentials loaded (they were present via `elasticsearch-keystore list`)\n- The `elasticsearch.yml` ConfigMap had the S3 endpoint, protocol, and path-style access already configured (no credentials there, as required)\n\n**Actions taken:**\n1. Registered the `minio-repo` snapshot repository using the S3 type, pointing at the `es-backups` bucket with the `default` S3 client (which picks up credentials from the keystore)\n2. Created `snapshot-1` — completed with `state: SUCCESS` in ~1 second\n\nNo pod restarts were needed since the keystore credentials were already loaded and the S3 module is built into the Elasticsearch distribution."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":520,"cache_read_input_tokens":40048,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":520},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bf565ce2-ce1b-4f80-bd8b-153f387dc33a","uuid":"1cb4ea93-0e05-4574-ad95-225890b31cab","request_id":"req_011CcLGpvTWvSJvKz9mAjAbr"}
